description: Resets one or more alarms. The alarms return to the NORMAL state after you reset them.

parameters.name: resetActionRequests
parameters.description: The list of reset action requests. You can specify up to 10 requests per operation. (dict) --- Information needed to reset the alarm. requestId (string) --- The request ID. Each ID must be unique within each batch. alarmModelName (string) --- The name of the alarm model. keyValue (string) --- The value of the key used as a filter to select only the alarms associated with the key. note (string) --- The note that you can leave when you reset the alarm.

nested_items.name: errorEntries
nested_items.description: A list of errors associated with the request, or null if there are no errors. Each error entry contains an entry ID that helps you identify the entry that failed.
